1) Configure Your Git User Information
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your.email@example.com"

2) Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/username/repository.git
cd repository

3) Open the file README.txt, make a minor change (e.g., add your name to the contributors list)
nano README.txt
Add your name to the contributors list, then save and exit.
git status

5) Stage the Changes You Made to README.txt for Commit
git add README.txt

git commit -m "Added my name to the contributors list"

git push origin main
git checkout -b feature/add-my-name
git log
